Chapter 16: The Mirror Vault
The hatch didn't swing open; it dissolved. The heavy alloy plates turned into a fine, grey mist that hung in the air like frozen breath. As Ren and Mira stepped inside, the roar of the "Gut" vanished, replaced by a silence so absolute it felt like pressure against their eardrums.
They weren't in a room. They were standing on a glass-like floor that stretched into an infinite horizon of darkness. Floating in the air around them were thousands of translucent, glowing cubes—each one containing a flickering image of a student, a lecture, or a combat session.
"It’s a library," Mira whispered, her voice barely a tremor. "But it’s... it’s all of us. Every memory we’ve had at the Academy."
Ren walked toward the center of the void. His [Entropy Sight] was screaming. The timers here weren't counting down; they were spinning in reverse.
