"Ren, look at the floor," Mira said, pointing down.
Beneath the glass surface, a massive, dark shape was pulsing. It looked like a giant, sleeping eye, miles wide, its pupil fixed directly on them. This was the 'Dormant Gate'. It wasn't a portal; it was a living, biological processor.
"The Black Box," Ren muttered, spotting a central pillar of obsidian rising from the eye's center.
As they approached the pillar, the air began to ripple. A figure stepped out of the static. It wasn't Vane, and it wasn't the monster-Aris.
It was Ren.
The figure wore the same Academy uniform, but its eyes were solid silver, and its skin was etched with glowing circuits that mirrored the 'Project Architect' sketches.
