"You’re late," the Mirror-Ren said. Its voice was a perfect, emotionless version of Ren’s own. "The 'Great Deletion' has already been scheduled. You are currently 41% of the way to the threshold."
"I'm here for the Black Box," Ren said, his hand tightening around the hilt of his invisible 'Logic Blade'.
"The Black Box isn't an object, Ren," the Avatar replied, stepping closer. Its feet didn't make a sound on the glass. "It’s a choice. The Association built this vault to store the 'errors' of humanity. They thought if they could filter out the chaos, they could create a perfect world. You are the result of that filter. You are the 'Zero' because you are the sum of everything they threw away."
Mira raised her staff, but the Avatar simply waved a hand, and her staff's light turned into a swarm of digital butterflies that dissipated into the dark.
"Mira!" Ren caught her as she stumbled.
"She is irrelevant to the calculation," the Avatar said. "Ren, the 'Administrator' is not an enemy. It is a function. If you take the Black Box, you don't defuse the bomb. You become the bomb. You will have the power to delete the Academy, the Association, and the Voids—but you will also delete the 'Veil' that keeps this reality separate from the Abyss."
