The Avatar tilted its head. "The logic does not allow for a third option."
"The logic was written by people who were afraid of the dark," Ren said. He reached into his jacket and pulled out the 'Project Architect' folder. He didn't read it. He began to tear the pages out, letting them fall onto the glass floor. "I’m not a filter. And I’m not an error."
Ren’s silver mark began to bleed black ink, covering his entire hand. He didn't aim for the Avatar. He knelt and slammed his hand against the glass floor, directly over the giant, sleeping eye.
"I’m the Architect," Ren growled. "And I’m 'Refactoring' the floor."
